body:
@ashvina - After several discussion, here is a proposal - 
- add an option in either client.yaml or scheduler.yaml for the additional classpaths.
- potentially override this with a cli option called --additional-scheduler-classpath or --additional-heron-classpath for all the CLI commands

@maosongfu - I am going to be putting up a PR with cli option

--extra-heron-classpath

This will be added to all the commands (except version and help). Let me know

the reason why python2.7 is required is because of pex and bazel. one thing we can do in all our python scripts is to use

#!/usr/bin/env python2.7

this will ensure all the scripts use python2.7 executable only. If python2.7 does not exist, it will bail out. Thoughts?

@billonahill - seems to have failed the test

```
//heron/instance/tests/java:spout-instance_unittest  ^[FAILED^[ in 22.5s
```

this is not a flaky test - not sure why.

@kramasamy if there's good reason why Exception needs to be caught, let's add an `IllegalCatch` exclude for the specific class to suppressions.xml:
https://github.com/twitter/heron/blob/master/tools/java/src/com/twitter/bazel/checkstyle/suppressions.xml#L10

Why the RegexpSingleline check fail? That one we should typically fix.
